<br>
My first fight with this weapon in hand was awesome. My melee damage was good, and while my fists were recycling the moonblade took over, hitting incredibly fast for 16hps each time. <br>
<br>
So, the fists alternate with the blade.<br>
<br>
However, it's bugged.<br>
<br>
After my first fight, I noticed my fists were no longer 'hitting'. So I took the blade off, in the middle of a fight. Then I just stood there while the mob beat on me. Nothing I did would resume my fists fighting.<br>
<br>
So, the next thing I did was, equip the blade again. The unequipped it.<br>
<br>
Next fight, my fists are back in action. During the fight I equip the blade, and sure enough, the blade alters with my fists.<br>
<br>
I did a whole mission testing this out, and my conclusion is you must unequip your blade after each fight. And re-equip it during your next fight ( a ROYAL pain in the arse ). <br>
<br>
There were some instances, where I did not un-equip the blade for the next fight but it functioned. I could not determine what the factor was for yet another variant of this bug.<br>
<br>
Has anyone out there found this to be true? And if so, how are you getting around this weapon/fist bug? Sounds very similar to the bow equip bug to me....<br>
<br>
Comments?<br>
<br>
